C<pre><code>typedef struct { 
    int a; 
    double d; 
} struct_t;

double fun(int i) { 
    volatile struct_t s; 
    s.d = 3.14; 
    s.a[i] = 1073741824; // Out-of-bounds access
    return s.d; 
}
</code></pre> Results: | Call      | Output                  | |-----------|-------------------------| | <code>fun(0)</code>  | <code>3.1400000000</code>          | | <code>fun(3)</code>  | <code>2.0000006104</code>          | | <code>fun(6)</code>  | Stack smashing detected | | <code>fun(8)</code>  | Segmentation fault      |   <p>Explanation: - Overwriting memory beyond <code>a</code> corrupts adjacent data (e.g., <code>d</code> or return addresses).  </p>

